title: For Sale/Trade:  Remington 725 .30-06 w/Leupold FXIII ☆SUPER RARE☆
postcontent:
Up for sale is a beautiful and incredibly rare Remington 725 chambered in .30-06 Springfield. The 725 was only produced four years, from 1958 to 1961 with only 7,700 chambered in .06.  They were discontinued at the end of '61 and replaced by the now legendary model 700. The 725 was the predecessor to the 700 and share many of the same features, including their rock solid "3 Rings of Steel" action. Basically the only difference in the two is the unique three position safety featured on the 725. It is equipped with a hinged floorplate, checkered walnut stock and decorative pistol grip cap. The original adjustable sights are still intact. Barrel code dates it as a January 1960 production. 

This beauty was obviously well taken care of. Looks as if the stock was refinished, but the original blueing is still deep and in excellent condition. The bore is bright and shiny, and this one is a real fine shooter. I put 20 rounds through it and was very impressed with its accuracy. This one would be perfect for the collector or the guy that wants to stand out in deer camp. Not too many of these rifles out there.

Mounted to the rifle is a top quality 2 year old 6X42 Leupold FXIII. The scope has a gloss finish and hand adjustable adjustments. Vintage Weaver off-set rings lock it place. Scope alone runs close to $500 new and like all FXIII/VXIII scopes, it has amazing glass and carries a full lifetime warranty. May separate from rifle for the right money. 

I know what these rifles bring and I'm not hard up for money, so I'm in no big hurry to sell. Open to trades for other quality firearms, especially centerfire rifles.

title: For Sale/Trade:  1948 Colt Woodsman Second Series Target Model
postcontent:
During WWII, Colt made Woodsman model pistols for the military to train soldiers with to save metal and powder. After the war, Colt used surplus military contract parts to assemble their Woodsman models. Once those parts ran out, they returned to the original wooden design grips. This is a military surplus parts model. Excellent shape. No scratches or dings. Only wearing is from holster wear. Super accurate shooter. True collectors item. This model can be found in auctions ranging from $800 to $1250 depending on quality. 

I've got a house full of kids to train now so a safe queen that I'm scared to let them touch just isn't practical any more.

title: For Sale:  TASER M26C W/LASER
postcontent: The TASER M26C uses replaceable cartridges which have 2 - 15' wires coiled inside, each with a sharp barb on the end.  Once fired, the barbs, or electrodes, are launched up to 15 feet towards your subject.  The barbs can penetrate up to 1" thick of clothing.  Once penetrated, either clothing or skin, the wires deliver the electric current to the subject.  While the voltage and amperage of a TASER Gun are lower than those of direct contact stun guns, the current is much more effective.  This is because TASER uses their patented Neuro-Muscular Incapacitation technology in their electrical current.  What this means is that the current the TASER Gun generates mimics that of the human body.  So, once the electrical current is delivered into the human body, the body's brain and central nervous system cannot discern what's going on and "freaks out".  The brain and nervous system doesn't know what to do.  Further, the M26C can also be used as a direct contact stun gun in a close encounter situation.  Simply pop out the cartridge and its ready for use as a stun gun.

The K-15 Kryptonyte Green laser is a modern styled laser for the modern rifle. The military styling and use of cutting edge technology makes this the best laser to put on the modern carbine rifle.
 The Kryptonyte Green Laser was designed for use with the modern rifle, carbine or any weapon with 3 inches of picatinny rail for mounting. Made out of aircraft grade 6061 aluminum with T3 hardness. The entire aluminum body is black anodized in a level 2 hardness. The concise laser engraved markings clearly shows all the user-friendly features.
